      "content": "While community organizing definitely demonstrates leadership and grit, the traditional markers in high-pressure corporate settings often favor experiences that mirror institutional rigor. Rowing and debate specifically showcase performance under highly structured, competitive deadlines, which is easily transferable to corporate metrics. Conversely, the skillset from community work is often perceived, albeit unfairly, as less \"unglamorous\" or immediately scalable within a strict corporate hierarchy. Ultimately, the fit depends on whether you value demonstrable competitive drive or demonstrated proactive community impact.",
