      "content": "i get the \"institutional rigor\" argument, but it feels like we're just saying \"white/wealthy\" activities are professional and anything else isn't. isn't it possible that the \"lack of scale\" or \"unglamorous\" label is just a way to dismiss people from different backgrounds or socio-economic levels? like, if candidate B was from a certain demographic, would we even be questioning their intensity, or would we just assume they're a \"community leader\" rather than a \"professional\"?",
